      "message": "[minor] Line 270: ЁЯЯб `onPushReceived()` calls `mAccountService.setAccountsActive(true)` which posts to `mExecutor`. If the daemon hasn\u0027t finished starting (e.g., `ensureDaemonStarted()` hasn\u0027t completed yet in the Firebase coroutine), this could race with daemon initialization. The Firebase handler calls `onPushReceived()` before `ensureDaemonStarted()`. The `daemon.isStarted` check provides some guard, but if the daemon is mid-start, it may be `true` while accounts aren\u0027t fully loaded yet. Consider moving the reactivation call to after `ensureDaemonStarted()` in the push handlers for safety.",
      "revId": "80e528980c2d03128df2d467c0ffe48d3c8dbc65",
