      "message": "[minor] Line 283: ЁЯЯб `scheduleIdleShutdown()` posts to the main-thread Handler, but it\u0027s being called from `mExecutor` (a background executor thread). `Handler.postDelayed` is thread-safe so it won\u0027t crash, but calling `scheduleIdleShutdown()` does an `enablePermanentService` check on the executor thread followed by a post to the main looper. This is fine functionally, but consider documenting thread-safety expectations for these public methods, or always dispatching to the main thread first for consistency.",
      "revId": "80e528980c2d03128df2d467c0ffe48d3c8dbc65",
